00:10:57,120 --> 00:11:00,080
你把苏玲的资料给我
You could just give me the file on Su Ling

170
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:03,120
我就会按你所说的做
and I would do what you request anyway.

171
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,680
行啊
Well, I could,

172
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:10,320
但有时候人需要被指引才会做正确的事情
but sometimes people need to be helped to do the right thing.

173
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:16,440
安委会的报告 尽快拿到 明白了吗?
That NSC report, as soon as you can, alright?

174
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:22,600
我就要这条了 谢谢
Ah, I'll take this one, please.

175
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:32,080
我知道一个事实 温斯顿在被谋杀前
I know for a fact that Winston was fearing for his life

176
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:34,040
很担心他的生命安全
before he was murdered.

177
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:37,760
所以你说错了 这不是一次随机抢劫
So this was not a random robbery like you said.

178
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:41,120
我可以看下那个案件的资料吗?
Is it possible for me to take a look at the case notes?

179
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,840
- 郑太太 - 我真的需要看下那个材料
- Mrs Cheng. - I really do need to look at them.

180
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:45,720
我不想让你们遗漏任何细节
I don't want you to have missed anything.

181
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,920
郑太太 抱歉 我们不能这样做
Mrs Cheng, I'm sorry. That's not the way we work.

182
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,400
那你们怎么做?
What is the way you work?

183
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:52,000
我丈夫在你管辖的区域内被谋杀
My husband was murdered on your streets.

184
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:54,280
什么进展都没有
Nothing has been done about it.

185
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,100
杀害他的凶手还逍遥法外 
His killer is out there, 

186
00:11:56,101 --> 00:11:57,760
吃喝玩乐 过着潇洒的生活
laughing, drinking, living his life

187
00:11:57,880 --> 00:12:00,120
而温斯顿却只能长眠地下
while Winston lies in his grave.

188
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,640
你让我怎么能安心入眠?
How do you suppose I sleep at night?

189
00:12:06,040 --> 00:12:07,840
你只能在这里看材料
They can't leave the station.

190
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,200
霍克
Ah, Hock.

191
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:30,920
温斯顿・郑的材料
Winston Cheng's file.

192
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:39,720
郑太太
Ah, Mrs Cheng.

193
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:42,840
很抱歉 您丈夫的材料好像不见了
I'm very sorry, but your husband's file appears to be missing.

194
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:46,640
这是什么意思?
What does that mean?

195
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:53,440
安吉的公寓就在这里
Angie's apartment is just here.

196
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:10,400
门上锁了
The door's locked.

197
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:14,280
别 别想了 老兄
No, don't even think about it, man.

198
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,560
你总是小瞧我
You always underestimate me.

199
00:13:16,680 --> 00:13:18,680
才没 我总是高估你
No, I overestimate you.

200
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:21,920
我觉得你会做得更聪明一点 更低调一点
I think you will do something smarter, and quieter.

201
00:13:22,040 --> 00:13:23,120
更安全一点!
Safer!

202
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:27,080
不是吧
Come on.

203
00:14:30,120 --> 00:14:31,400
哇哦!
Whoa!

204
00:14:36,160 --> 00:14:38,440
别动 好吗? 别动
Relax, OK? Just relax.

205
00:14:43,880 --> 00:14:45,760
为什么你不拦住他?
Why didn't you stop him?

206
00:14:45,920 --> 00:14:48,800
你以为我没拦么?
What do you think I was doing?

207
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:52,600
别担心 下次再见到他 我就认出来了
Don't worry. I see him again, I'll know him.

208
00:14:52,760 --> 00:14:55,840
- 是吗? - 没错
- Yeah? - Yeah.

209
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:58,840
什么掉了?


210
00:14:58,840 --> 00:15:00,840
是他耳朵啦


211
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,440
他到底在找什么呢?
What was he looking for, anyway?

212
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:07,720
嘿! 拿着啦! 嘿!
Hey! Hey, hold it, lah! Hey!

213
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,720
嘿
Hey.

214
00:15:21,400 --> 00:15:22,960
这些都是什么?
What is all that?

215
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,960
看起来像监视时拍的照片
They look like surveillance photos.

216
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,480
找到一个写满名字和数字的名单
It's a list of names and numbers.

217
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:34,240
肯定是她在调查的东西
Must be something she was working on.

218
00:15:37,520 --> 00:15:38,880
嘿
Hey.

219
00:15:39,040 --> 00:15:43,120
不管那人找的是什么 肯定不是钱
Whatever that guy was looking for, it's definitely not money.

220
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:47,440
他肯定在找什么东西
He was definitely looking for something.

221
00:16:01,160 --> 00:16:03,600
康
Kang.

222
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:04,760
嗯?
Hmm?

223
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:12,800
是大麻
It's hash.

224
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,520
迈卡
Macca.

225
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,080
没空呢 山姆
Not now, Sam.

226
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,200
我得把这个先打完
I've really got to get this filed.

227
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,400
她在写什么呢 迈卡?
What was she writing, Macca?

228
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,840
她家里到处都是照片 名字和数字
She had photos, names and numbers everywhere.

229
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:30,360
可我从没看见一份报道
I never saw a story.

230
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:32,960
她把东西给我了 只是草稿
No, she gave it to me. Rough draft, anyway.

231
00:16:33,080 --> 00:16:34,360
是什么呢?
What was it?

232
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:38,040
她痴迷于秘密帮派
She was obsessed with the Secret Societies.

233
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:40,680
想追踪新加坡毒品的交易链
Wanted to track the movement of drugs through Singapore.

234
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,880
我告诉她这事儿没戏
I told her it was a dead-end story.

235
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:45,800
证据难找 也没证人 就别做了
Hard to prove, no-one to talk to, and to let it go.

236
00:16:45,920 --> 00:16:47,280
她放弃了吗?
Did she?

237
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:51,760
山姆 这跟你朋友刺杀她又没关系
Sam, this has got nothing to do with your mate stabbing her.

238
00:16:51,880 --> 00:16:53,480
毒品报道跟这无关
The drug story is irrelevant.

239
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:55,480
那为什么她家里会藏有
Then why was she hiding a trafficable amount of hash

240
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,960
可供买卖量的大麻呢?
in her apartment?

241
00:17:01,920 --> 00:17:04,520
安吉不会沾染毒品的 她不喜欢
Ange would never touch drugs. She hated them.

242
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:07,800
她只想成为记者
All she ever wanted was to be a journo.

243
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,560
还是去问你朋友大麻是怎么进她家的吧
So you ask your mate how that hash got into her place.

244
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:12,800
- 得了吧 - 接着说
- Oh, come on. - Go on.

245
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:14,920
我敢说十有八九毒品是他的
I'll give you ten to one it's his.

246
00:17:15,080 --> 00:17:18,680
他肯定也不会承认
And I'll give you five to one that he lies about it.

247
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:23,080
而且我确定不管怎样你都会相信他
And I'll give you even money that you'll believe him anyway.

248
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:24,480
是啊 无所谓了
Yeah, whatever.

249
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:28,760
不 当然不是
No, absolutely not.

250
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:31,000
所以你从没在新加坡进行大麻交易?
So you never moved hash in and out of Singapore?

251
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:32,880
跟我发誓毒品的事跟你无关
Swear to me you're not involved in drugs.

252
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:34,000
我发誓 真没有
I swear. Never.

253
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:35,480
因为我看到一个记者
'Cause I'm looking at a reporter

254
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:37,520
在调查港口的毒品交易
investigating the drug trade on the docks,

255
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,680
也跟一个跑货船的男人在一起
hanging out with a guy who works on freighters.

256
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:41,200
这都说得通 对吧?
It all adds up, doesn't it?

257
00:17:41,360 --> 00:17:44,640
她的确问了我关于毒品的问题
Well, she asked me questions about it, sure.

258
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:46,680
我们就是这样见面的
I mean, that's how we met.

259
00:17:46,840 --> 00:17:49,960
她在那里跟船员和港口人员交谈
She's down there talking to sailors and dockies.

260
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:53,200
那些人嘴巴很严 不干活的时候也不多话
Those blokes don't talk, even if they're not moving stuff.

261
00:17:56,440 --> 00:18:01,420
山姆 如果你想要放弃这个案子我也能理解
Sam, I can understand if you wanna give up.

262
00:18:04,200 --> 00:18:06,120
告诉我这不是你干的
Tell me you didn't do this.

263
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:12,560
这不是我干的
I didn't do this.

264
00:18:14,720 --> 00:18:16,440
但你也不记得了
But you can't remember.

265
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:20,360
对
No.

266
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:25,880
也许这里有什么猫腻 有些互动
Maybe there's something in here, some kind of contact.

267
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:27,920
我是说 她在挖掘毒品交易内幕
I mean, she's digging into the drug trade.

268
00:18:28,080 --> 00:18:30,040
可能她走得比迈卡想得还远
Maybe she got further than Macca thought.

269
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:33,400
你是说她在跟踪这个事情 太过头了
You're saying she was following a story, got too close,

270
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:36,360
以至于她调查的某些人把她杀了
and someone she was investigating killed her.

271
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:40,920
这个人偷溜进她的房间
And this person sneaked into her room,

272
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:45,280
绕过睡在她旁边的你朋友 把她捅死
past your friend who was sleeping next to her, stabbed her to death

273
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,440
而你朋友完全没有醒过来?
and your friend didn't wake up?

274
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,800
那些大麻怎么说呢?
And what about the drugs?

275
00:18:49,960 --> 00:18:51,800
可能是调查的一部分
Maybe it was part of the investigation.

276
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:54,080
- 也许她自己买的 - 买那么多?
- Maybe she bought some. - That much?

277
00:18:56,080 --> 00:18:59,560
有没有可能你朋友在撒谎?
Is it possible you got it wrong about your friend?

278
00:18:59,680 --> 00:19:01,480
所有人都觉得他在撒谎
Everyone thinks he did it.

279
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:04,360
你回来啦! 这个 你跟他说了吗?
You're back! Here, did you tell him?

280
00:19:04,520 --> 00:19:05,840
还没呢
Not yet.

281
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,440
关于温斯顿叔叔的 案子材料不见了
About Uncle Winston. The missing case file.

282
00:19:08,560 --> 00:19:10,120
这是关于温斯顿什么的?
What's this about Winston?

283
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:12,320
好的 我会转告他的
Yes, of course. I'll tell him.

284
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:15,800
澳大利亚高级专员想要见你
The Australian High Commissioner wants to see you.

285
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:18,720
你先去吧 我晚点告诉你
Well, you go. I'll tell you later.

286
00:19:31,840 --> 00:19:34,200
这得要一整天 所以只要我们...
They're taking all day, so as long as we...

287
00:19:34,360 --> 00:19:35,960
塔克沃思女士
Lady Tuckworth.

288
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:38,400
辛普森夫人?
Mrs Simpson?

289
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:40,160
卡拉汉先生
Mr Callaghan.

290
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:42,720
我这几天住在这儿
I'm just staying here for a few days.

291
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:45,960
是啊 她丈夫出差了 我陪陪她
Yes, just company while her husband's away.

292
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,360
出门啊?
Heading off?

293
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,400
是啊 我们去买机票
Yes, we're just going to get some tickets.

294
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:52,240
机票?
Tickets?

295
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,680
是的 克莱尔的母亲生病了
Yes, Claire's mother's been taken ill

296
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:58,280
她要回悉尼待一段时间
and she's just going to spend a little time in Sydney.

297
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:01,760
你母亲? 我记得她过世了
Your mother? I was sure she died.

298
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:04,080
没有 你肯定记错了
No, you must be mistaken.

299
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,760
我丈夫在等你吧
I believe my husband's waiting for you.

300
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:12,120
很高兴见到你 卡拉汉先生
It's lovely to see you, Mr Callaghan.

301
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:13,160
我也是
Yes.

302
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:23,880
那么 你是那个澳大利亚特约记者
Now, you're a mate of this Australian stringer,

303
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,520
布鲁斯・麦克唐纳的朋友吗?
Bruce Macdonald?

304
00:20:25,680 --> 00:20:27,200
迈卡 是的 没错
Ah, Macca, that's right. Yeah, right.

305
00:20:27,360 --> 00:20:29,400
我需要你去告诉他不要这么关注
I need you to tell him to pull his head in

306
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:30,880
这个被谋杀的女孩的新闻了
over this murdered girl story.

307
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:35,240
堪培拉正试图敏感对待这些黑色议题
Canberra's trying to be a little bit sensitive to the black issue.

308
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,360
现在公民投票还悬而未决
There's a referendum in the air.

309
00:20:37,480 --> 00:20:40,720
不要因为这件事惹麻烦
So now is not the time to have

310
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:45,280
现在不是时候
this particular piece of excrement hitting the fan.

311
00:20:45,440 --> 00:20:49,200
跟我相比 他可能更听你的话
Well, he's more likely to listen to you than me.

312
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:52,640
听着 我不是让他不写这个报道了
Look, I'm not asking him not to write the story, you know,

313
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:54,760
只是缓和一下
just tone it down a bit.

314
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,720
那个家伙显然罪不可赦
The bloke's obviously as guilty as sin.

315
00:20:56,840 --> 00:20:58,400
先生 我不这么认为
Sir, I don't think he is.

316
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:01,840
我最近在调查这个情况 我认为不是他杀了她
I've been investigating the situation and I don't think he killed her.

317
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,320
真的吗?
Really?

318
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:06,280
是啊 你是个侦探
Well, you're a detective

319
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:09,720
这事根本轮不上我班门弄斧
and far be it for me to tell you how to suck eggs,

320
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:12,360
但是 有什么证据呢?
but, er, what about the evidence, hmm?

321
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:14,200
一个原住民
Abo.

322
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:15,840
喝了酒
Booze.

323
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,240
一个女人 死了
Woman, dead.

324
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,560
罗伯特・科利尔被誉为战争英雄
Robert Collier's a decorated war hero.

325
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,240
真的吗?
Really?

326
00:21:21,360 --> 00:21:22,600
他在三九年入伍
He signed up in '39.

327
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,600
第二陆军部 第二武装部队
WO2, 2nd AIF.

328
00:21:24,760 --> 00:21:28,160
他荣誉地服役 获得了勇敢和服务奖章
He served with distinction. Medals for bravery and service.

329
00:21:28,280 --> 00:21:30,880
这样啊
Right.

330
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,920
天啊
Oh, Jesus.

331
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:35,880
"土著战争英雄被陷害"
'Aboriginal War Hero Framed'.

332
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:39,560
那可不是我想看到的头条
That's the last headline I want to see.

333
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:43,360
如果你能释放他 我就能找出事情的真相
Well, if you can get him out, I can find out what really happened.

334
00:22:45,920 --> 00:22:47,680
哈里森
Harrison.

335
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,760
你在干什么?
What are you doing?

336
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:56,080
我只是确保我有你想要的文件的拷贝
I was just making sure that I had copies of those files you wanted.

337
00:22:56,240 --> 00:22:58,760
好样的 我现在就看
Oh, good for you. I'll look at 'em right now.

338
00:23:00,760 --> 00:23:02,280
好的
OK.

339
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:11,680
这样吧 我最好去接电话 一会再和你聊
Actually, I'd better get this. I'll catch up with you later.

340
00:23:18,920 --> 00:23:21,280
- 谢谢 山姆 你好样的 - 这只是保释
- Thanks, Sam, you're a champion. - It's only bail.

341
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:23,080
在你的听证会之前还有很多事情要做
Got a lot of work before your committal hearing.

342
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:25,680
因为澳洲政府忙着拉皮条没空伸张正义...
Any comment on getting away with murder because the Australian Government's...

343
00:23:25,840 --> 00:23:27,560
- 迈卡! - 就让犯人逍遥法外...
- Macca! - ...is too busy pandering...

344
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:28,698
把他带回我那里 
