00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:29,840
是的
Yeah.

526
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:31,920
那是罗伯的服役号
That's Robbo's service number.

527
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,840
- 搞定了 - 修好了吗?
- There you go. - Looking good?

528
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:39,600
是的 应该是好了
Yeah, that should do it.

529
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:41,200
来 试试
Here, try that one.

530
00:33:41,360 --> 00:33:43,600
天哪 真合适 谢谢你
Oh, my God, it fits so perfectly. Thank you.

531
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:45,320
不客气
No worries.

532
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,280
请用
Here.

533
00:33:48,400 --> 00:33:49,880
谢谢
Thank you.

534
00:33:51,080 --> 00:33:53,200
你在船上工作吗?
So you work on the ships?

535
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:56,568
你就是那样认识山姆的吗? 
So that's how you know Sam? 

536
00:33:56,569 --> 00:33:57,960
在他做进出口工作时?
From his import-export work?

537
00:33:58,080 --> 00:34:01,640
不 不是的 我...
Well, no, not exactly. I...

538
00:34:01,760 --> 00:34:04,080
我很久以前就认识他了
I've known him for a long time.

539
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:08,280
警察先生
Inspector.

540
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:09,840
有何贵干?
What is your business here?

541
00:34:11,160 --> 00:34:14,440
罗伯特・安德鲁・科利尔 我是来逮捕你的
Robert Andrew Collier, I'm placing you under arrest.

542
00:34:14,560 --> 00:34:16,880
但他刚被保释出狱
But he's just been released on bail.

543
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:18,600
我们有新证据了
We have new evidence.

544
00:34:18,720 --> 00:34:20,280
保释被驳回了
Bail's been revoked.

545
00:34:20,400 --> 00:34:21,760
请站起来
Stand up, please.

546
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:30,040
嘿 嘿 站住!
Hey, hey, stop!

547
00:34:30,160 --> 00:34:31,240
站住!
Stop!

548
00:34:49,840 --> 00:34:51,960
你让我像是个傻瓜一样
You made me look like a dick.

549
00:34:52,120 --> 00:34:55,440
走了那么多关系 托人帮忙 安排保释
Pulled all these strings, called in favours, organised bail.

550
00:34:55,600 --> 00:34:56,968
可你的朋友却畏罪潜逃  
Now your mate's done a runner.  

551
00:34:56,969 --> 00:34:57,880
不是他干的 先生
Sir, he didn't do it.

552
00:34:58,000 --> 00:34:59,960
那他为什么要逃?
Well, why did he run, hmm?

553
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:03,560
正如我们所说 现在你的另一朋友又要在公爵
Now your other mate's down at the Duke as we speak

554
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:06,800
炮制下一个大新闻
banging out his next big story.

555
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:08,960
我都不敢去想明天的头条会是什么
I don't even want to guess what the headline is,

556
00:35:09,120 --> 00:35:12,720
但我猜'土著居民'和'畏罪潜逃'
but I would suspect that 'Aborigine' and 'walkabout'

557
00:35:12,840 --> 00:35:15,080
会是关键词
will feature fairly largely.

558
00:35:16,680 --> 00:35:21,480
听着 如果你坚信他是清白的
Look, if you are convinced this man is innocent,

559
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:24,720
那就找些证据出来
then find some bloody evidence.

560
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:27,280
我可以告诉你的是
And I can tell you this.

561
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:30,198
如果是他杀害了那个澳大利亚女孩 
If he's murdered an Australian girl, 

562
00:35:30,199 --> 00:35:32,440
那战争英雄的头衔也救不了他
being a war hero will not help him.

563
00:35:43,160 --> 00:35:45,960
等等 你去哪?
Wait. Where are you going?

564
00:35:46,120 --> 00:35:51,060
爸爸说 如果情况有变 就在家里碰头
Dad said, if anything goes wrong, meet at the house.

565
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:01,240
你不能待在这
You can't stay here.

566
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:02,600
这里没有吃的
There's no food.

567
00:36:02,720 --> 00:36:04,440
我能找到吃的
I can get food.

568
00:36:06,480 --> 00:36:08,240
这人是谁?
Who this man?

569
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:10,160
你又是谁?
Who the hell are you?

570
00:36:10,320 --> 00:36:13,040
他是翁叔叔 我一直问他要吃的
This is Uncle Weng. I've been getting food off him.

571
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:15,400
从战俘监狱里来的?
From the camp?

572
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:20,520
你从战俘监狱溜到城市里来的?
You snuck into the city from the prison camp?

573
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:22,520
总得有人这么做
Someone had to.

574
00:36:22,640 --> 00:36:24,240
我要回店里去了
I've got to get back to the shop.

575
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:25,720
你一个人没问题吗?
You sure you're OK?

576
00:36:34,600 --> 00:36:36,160
你这样过多久了?
How long you been doing this?

577
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:38,440
自从妈妈被杀后就一直这样过了
Since Mum got murdered.

578
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:09,000
看来你还真不愧是个侦探 对吧?
So you really are some sort of detective, eh?

579
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:16,520
我想如果我是个好侦探 我就应该先来这里
I suppose if I were any good, I would have come here first.

580
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:21,480
知道吗 当你第一次带我来这时
You know, when you first brought me here,

581
00:37:21,600 --> 00:37:25,040
我以为你在战争前
I thought that you must have been

582
00:37:25,200 --> 00:37:27,960
一定是个被宠坏的小家伙
one hell of a spoilt brat before the war.

583
00:37:29,520 --> 00:37:32,320
所以你才无法面对
Thought that's why you couldn't face the fact

584
00:37:32,440 --> 00:37:34,560
爸爸回不了家这一事实
that your dad wasn't coming home.

585
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:36,720
你总是有你自己的行事方式
I mean, you always had your own way.

586
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:38,680
是的
Yeah.

587
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:45,360
现在我觉得真相很难去面对...
Now I'm thinking truth can be a hard thing to face...

588
00:37:48,920 --> 00:37:52,888
...不管你是四五年时的小伙
...whether you're a young lad in '45 

589
00:37:52,889 --> 00:37:55,440
还是六四年时的老兵
or an old soldier in '64.

590
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:02,760
那你准备怎么办? 回到船上吗?
So what do you wanna do? Get back on the boat?

591
00:38:05,360 --> 00:38:07,600
船今晚就开
Ship sails tonight.

592
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:10,120
船长是我的朋友
The captain's a mate.

593
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:12,240
他能帮我移民出去
He can get me through immigration.

594
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:18,160
那你就再也回不来了
You could never come back.

595
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:30,520
是的
The truth.

596
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:36,000
你有计划?
You got a plan?

597
00:38:36,120 --> 00:38:38,160
是的
Yeah.

598
00:38:39,840 --> 00:38:41,840
那就赶快开始吧
Then you'd better get cracking.

599
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:04,000
你到这来里来过 记得吗?
So you came here. You remember that?

600
00:39:04,120 --> 00:39:07,200
是的 虽然不是很清楚
Yeah, it's not clear as day.

601
00:39:07,360 --> 00:39:09,400
但回忆起来不是问题
But that's not the bit I'm having problems with.

602
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:10,880
你们做了些什么?
And what were you doing?

603
00:39:11,040 --> 00:39:14,720
安吉和我在外面买了些东西吃
Well, Ange and I got something to eat outside,

604
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:17,600
我喂她吃鸡爪
and I fed her a chook's foot.

605
00:39:18,880 --> 00:39:21,480
然后进来喝酒除除味道
And we came in here to wash the taste out.

606
00:39:25,840 --> 00:39:28,880
你记得和谁说过话吗?
Do you remember talking to someone?

607
00:39:29,000 --> 00:39:30,640
年轻的马来人?
Young Malay bloke?

608
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:32,840
没有
No.

609
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:37,680
我认为他在你们酒里下了药
I think he spiked your drink.

610
00:39:41,560 --> 00:39:43,240
好吧 这之后呢?
Alright, what happened after that?

611
00:39:45,080 --> 00:39:48,080
安吉觉得头有点晕
Well, Ange was feeling a little dizzy.

612
00:39:49,680 --> 00:39:51,840
我们就出去透透气
We went out to get some fresh air.

613
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:54,080
- 你们这就出去了? - 是的
- So you left? - Yeah.

614
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:57,720
好的 那你们走的哪条路?
OK, so which way did you go?

615
00:39:57,840 --> 00:40:01,520
从这走的
Ah, through this way.

616
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:17,160
有只 猴子在跳舞
There was, er, a monkey dancing in the street.

617
00:40:31,920 --> 00:40:33,720
那边
That way.

618
00:40:33,840 --> 00:40:36,040
她说这是近路
She said it was a short cut.

619
00:40:42,080 --> 00:40:44,480
有几个人在这里赌博
There was a bunch of guys gambling through here.

620
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:49,280
这扇门
This door.

621
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:01,680
那个炒面男
The chow mein guy.

622
00:41:03,760 --> 00:41:04,800
什么?
The what?

623
00:41:04,920 --> 00:41:07,520
炒面男 他在这里
The chow mein guy, he was there.

624
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:11,600
- 有打斗吗? - 不 不 没那回事
- Was it a fight? - Oh, no, no, nothing like that.

625
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:17,160
我们继续走
We just kept on walking.

626
00:41:22,200 --> 00:41:23,800
就这样了
And that's it.

627
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:27,640
我能记起的下一件事 就是我在她身边醒来
Next thing I know, I woke up next to her.

628
00:41:27,760 --> 00:41:30,040
一定还有其他的情况
There's got to be something else.

629
00:41:30,160 --> 00:41:32,840
安吉家在拐角处
Ange's place is around the corner.

630
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:35,000
肯定有什么事在这里发生
Whatever it was had to have happened here.

631
00:41:35,120 --> 00:41:36,440
就在这里
Right here.

632
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:42,440
听着 这是个好主意
Look, it was a good idea.

633
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:45,680
- 好方法 - 继续想 罗伯 拜托了
- A good try. - Keep thinking, Robbo. Come on.

634
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:48,000
你在这里 安吉在这里
You were here, Ange was here.

635
00:41:48,120 --> 00:41:49,840
也许我不想查出真相
Maybe I don't want to find out.

636
00:41:49,960 --> 00:41:52,160
也许是我干的
Maybe I did it.

637
00:41:52,320 --> 00:41:54,600
也许除了这点什么也发现不了
Maybe there's nothing to find out except that.

638
00:41:57,640 --> 00:41:59,680
也许是你干的
Maybe you did.

639
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,960
你不想确定一下吗?
Don't you want to know for sure?

640
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:21,120
怎么了?
What is it?

641
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:22,520
想起一些东西
Something.

642
00:42:32,560 --> 00:42:35,040
她休息了一下
She rested.

643
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:36,480
安吉
Ange.

644
00:42:36,600 --> 00:42:37,840
安吉在这里休息
Ange rested here.

645
00:42:41,240 --> 00:42:43,160
当时我在这里
And I was here.

646
00:42:48,320 --> 00:42:50,160
炒面男
The chow mein guy.

647
00:43:20,400 --> 00:43:22,200
你的包!
Your bag!

648
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:24,000
别管它了
Don't worry about it.

649
00:43:25,560 --> 00:43:27,040
你还好吗?
You OK?

650
00:43:27,160 --> 00:43:32,080
我们回... 家吧
Let's get... home.

651
00:43:45,280 --> 00:43:48,720
我没想到有那么严重
I didn't realise it was that serious.

652
00:43:50,480 --> 00:43:52,320
你不可能知道的
Well, you couldn't have known.

653
00:43:52,440 --> 00:43:54,520
我本可以做点什么的
Well, I could have done something.

654
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:56,920
- 我本可以求助的 - 不过你被下药了
- I could have called for help. - But you were drugged.

655
00:43:59,080 --> 00:44:01,120
你没杀他 罗伯 是这个人干的
You didn't kill her, Robbo. This other guy did.

656
00:44:04,400 --> 00:44:07,080
就因为我们撞到了他?
Because we bumped him?

657
00:44:07,200 --> 00:44:09,160
只是运气不好罢了
It was just bad luck.

658
00:44:09,280 --> 00:44:12,120
错误的时间错误的地点
Wrong place at the wrong time.

659
00:44:14,480 --> 00:44:16,560
你记得他的相貌吗?
You remember his face?

660
00:44:23,120 --> 00:44:27,320
是的 我记得
Yeah, I remember his face.

661
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:37,800
下午好 哈里森 进展得怎么样了?
Good afternoon, Harrison. How did you get on?

662
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:41,400
我拿到你想要的东西了
I got what you wanted.

663
00:44:41,520 --> 00:44:42,800
太棒了
Excellent.

664
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:45,080
我会继续做你交给我的事
And I'm going to keep on doing as you ask.

665
00:44:45,240 --> 00:44:47,749
不过我知道你的本质... 
But I see you for what you are... 

666
00:44:47,750 --> 00:44:49,680
一个虚伪卑鄙的英国佬
a slimy limey turd.

667
00:44:49,840 --> 00:44:52,612
我真心希望你趁太阳还没下山 
I really hope that you enjoy the sunshine 

668
00:44:52,613 --> 00:44:53,800
好好欣赏阳光
while it lasts,

669
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:57,480
因为总有一天 农奴会翻身做主人的
because one day the boot's going to be on the other foot.

670
00:45:21,240 --> 00:45:23,160
好像是那个人
That looks like him.

671
00:45:40,240 --> 00:45:42,120
你记得我吗?
You remember me?

672
00:45:56,080 --> 00:45:58,480
整件事不过是一个很遗憾的故事
The whole thing's just a sorry story.

673
00:45:58,640 --> 00:46:02,400
他生气了 赶上他们 想抢走安吉的包
I mean, he got angry, went after 'em, tried to snatch Ange's bag.

674
00:46:02,560 --> 00:46:04,720
她没意识到她伤得多严重
She didn't realise how badly she'd been hurt.

675
00:46:04,880 --> 00:46:06,800
- 这故事不错 - 搜搜他的住所
- Good story. - Search his apartment.

676
00:46:06,920 --> 00:46:08,480
说不定能找到她的包
Maybe you'll find her bag.

677
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:10,400
你把刀扫描了吗?
You pull any prints off the knife?

678
00:46:10,520 --> 00:46:12,000
我肯定上面全是方的指纹
I bet Fong's are all over it.

679
00:46:12,120 --> 00:46:13,680
是他干的 阿姆兰
He's the one, Amran.

680
00:46:13,800 --> 00:46:15,320
不是罗伯
Not Robbo.

681
00:46:15,480 --> 00:46:19,120
- 你朋友确定是那个人? - 对
- Your friend's sure it was that guy? - Oh, yeah.

682
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:25,040
- 我会调查清楚的 - 好的
- I'll look into it. - OK.

683
00:46:29,760 --> 00:46:31,840
真为你朋友高兴
Very pleased for your mate.

684
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:33,800
你可以自己告诉他啊
Well, you could tell him yourself.

685
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:37,030
你也知道 我有好多事要干 
Oh, well, you know, so much to do. 

686
00:46:37,031 --> 00:46:38,920
邮件 外交函件啊
Mail, diplomatic correspondence.

687
00:46:39,280 --> 00:46:42,200
另外 我得给这个女孩的父母写一份官方报告
Plus, I need to write an official report for the girl's parents.

688
00:46:42,320 --> 00:46:45,080
不过拜托你 把我的问候带给他
But please, give the man my best.

689
00:46:45,200 --> 00:46:47,000
罗伯特・科利尔
Robert Collier.

690
00:46:49,360 --> 00:46:51,680
对 没错 是科利尔
Yes, Collier. Exactly.

691
00:46:53,720 --> 00:46:56,160
她们来了
Ah. Here they are.

692
00:46:56,320 --> 00:47:00,000
现在 她们要过来喝点开胃酒了
Now, they will be down here for an aperitif shortly.

693
00:47:00,120 --> 00:47:01,280
你想留下来吗?
Would you care to stay?

694
00:47:01,400 --> 00:47:03,120
不行 我要去见一个人
Oh, I can't. I'm meeting someone.

695
00:47:03,240 --> 00:47:05,160
真聪明啊
Wise man.

696
00:47:06,400 --> 00:47:10,160
接下来的事 我们称之为外交事件
Now, there's what you call a diplomatic incident.

697
00:47:10,320 --> 00:47:13,360
要是你想跟小白脸鬼混
If you're going to go wild with the pool boy,

698
00:47:13,520 --> 00:47:16,160
老天 可千万别告诉你丈夫
for God's sake, don't tell the husband.

699
00:47:24,480 --> 00:47:26,680
不论如何 再次谢谢你 卡拉汉
Anyhow, thanks again, Callaghan.

700
00:47:49,040 --> 00:47:51,400
安吉 她是个好女孩
She was a good girl, Ange.

701
00:47:52,880 --> 00:47:54,680
很聪明
Bright.

702
00:47:57,320 --> 00:48:00,240
她面前有大好的前程
She had the whole world in front of her.

703
00:48:03,480 --> 00:48:05,440
我不敢相信她已经死了
I can't believe she's dead.

704
00:48:06,720 --> 00:48:11,720
就因为 有个家伙 这...
All because what, some bloke, what...

705
00:48:13,840 --> 00:48:16,200
这叫什么 命该如此还是只是运气不好?
What's that, fate or just dumb luck?

706
00:48:19,880 --> 00:48:21,025
不管是什么 
Whatever it is, 

707
00:48:21,026 --> 00:48:24,080
它让你在四五年的时候为我停下来了
it made you stop for me in '45.

708
00:48:31,640 --> 00:48:33,080
一路顺风 大哥
Sail well, brother.

709
00:48:34,240 --> 00:48:35,800
谢谢 兄弟
Thanks, mate.

710
00:48:48,720 --> 00:48:50,880
你的朋友正式清白了
Your friend's officially in the clear.

711
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:52,560
李库方被控告了
Lee Kum Fong's been charged.

712
00:48:52,720 --> 00:48:55,280
我们在他的住所找到了女孩的包
We found the girl's handbag at his place.

713
00:48:55,400 --> 00:48:57,440
下药的人应该能找到他
The drink spiker was able to ID him.

714
00:48:57,600 --> 00:48:59,400
关于指纹你也说对了
And you were right about those prints.

715
00:48:59,520 --> 00:49:00,880
你听上去很惊讶
You sound surprised.

716
00:49:01,040 --> 00:49:02,680
我以为你想让方进监狱
Well, I thought you might have your own reasons

717
00:49:02,800 --> 00:49:04,160
可能有你自己的原因
for wanting Fong in jail.

718
00:49:04,320 --> 00:49:07,240
- 为什么? - 杀害温斯顿的凶手
- Why? - Winston's murder.

719
00:49:07,400 --> 00:49:09,200
李库方是其中一个嫌疑人
Lee Kum Fong was one of the suspects.

720
00:49:09,360 --> 00:49:12,280
那晚有人看见他在现场 这是他的风格
He was seen in the area that night. It's his style.

721
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:13,720
杯子里藏了把刀
Mugging with a knife.

722
00:49:13,880 --> 00:49:15,920
我不确定他是唯一的嫌疑人
I wasn't too sure and he wasn't the only suspect.

723
00:49:16,040 --> 00:49:17,440
不过我已经盯上他了
But I had my eye on him.

724
00:49:17,600 --> 00:49:19,480
你认为李库方杀了温斯顿・郑?
You think Lee Kum Fong killed Winston Cheng?

725
00:49:19,600 --> 00:49:20,960
我觉得有这个可能
I think it's possible.

726
00:49:24,080 --> 00:49:27,680
我们查了温斯顿被杀时正在调查的所有案件
We've been going back through all the cases Winston was working on

727
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:31,040
没提到方啊
when he was killed, and there was no mention of Fong.

728
00:49:31,200 --> 00:49:33,360
第一次 我们有了嫌疑人
Well, for the first time, we've got a suspect.

729
00:49:33,520 --> 00:49:35,320
方可能是唯一一个
Fong could be the only person who knows

730
00:49:35,440 --> 00:49:36,800
知道当晚温斯顿情况的人
what happened to Winston that night.

731
00:49:36,920 --> 00:49:38,440
我们得从他开始
We've got to start with him.

732
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:40,360
明天一早我就去找他谈
I'll talk to him first thing tomorrow.

733
00:49:40,480 --> 00:49:42,960
好的
Yeah, alright.

734
00:49:45,040 --> 00:49:46,760
山姆?
Oh, Sam?

735
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:52,640
你朋友 辛普森夫人
Um, your friend, Mrs Simpson.

736
00:49:52,760 --> 00:49:55,560
我听说她要离开新加坡了
I've heard she's leaving Singapore.

737
00:49:55,680 --> 00:49:57,280
你知道这事儿吗?
Do you know that?

738
00:49:59,360 --> 00:50:01,240
明天一早
First thing tomorrow morning.

739
00:50:46,520 --> 00:50:49,760
好了 抱歉耽误了这么久
Here you go. Sorry that took so long.

740
00:50:53,040 --> 00:50:55,520
失陪一下
Excuse me.

741
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:56,760
嘿
Hey.

742
00:50:58,760 --> 00:51:00,360
山姆?
Sam?

743
00:51:03,320 --> 00:51:04,920
她在这吗?
Is she here?

744
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:09,440
要是我告诉你她在呢?
And what if I told you that she was?

745
00:51:12,240 --> 00:51:14,080
山姆
Oh, Sam.

746
00:51:15,200 --> 00:51:17,480
你能给她带来什么呢?
I mean, what can you offer her?

747
00:51:18,760 --> 00:51:21,560
什么 唐人街的一个房间?
What is it, a room in Chinatown?

748
00:51:23,360 --> 00:51:27,440
她失去了她的婚姻 她的家庭 她的朋友
She'd lose her marriage, her family, her friends.

749
00:51:27,560 --> 00:51:29,520
她没有工作
She'd have no job.

750
00:51:29,640 --> 00:51:32,440
我是说 她能怎么做呢?
I mean, what would she do?

751
00:51:35,040 --> 00:51:38,720
你知道 要是你真的爱她...
You know, if you really love her...

752
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:45,880
...你也许应该想想怎么做对她最好
...you might consider just doing what's best for her.

753
00:51:55,120 --> 00:51:57,400
我不会告诉她你来过
I won't tell her that you were here.

754
00:52:13,560 --> 00:52:15,480
重要的不是你这么做了
It's not that you did it.

755
00:52:15,640 --> 00:52:17,680
而是他拿什么威胁你让你这么做的
It's whatever he's got on you that made you do it.

756
00:52:17,840 --> 00:52:19,160
我在建议他们把你安排到别的地方
I'm recommending they post you somewhere else.

757
00:52:19,280 --> 00:52:20,760
对不起我对你撒谎了
I'm sorry that I lied to you.

758
00:52:20,920 --> 00:52:23,440
如果我问你一个问题 是想得到诚实的答案
If I ask you a question, I expect an honest answer.

759
00:52:23,560 --> 00:52:24,640
日安 弗兰克
G'day, Frank.

760
00:52:24,800 --> 00:52:26,720
周五晚上 我们会永远离开新加坡
On Friday night, we're leaving Singapore for good.

761
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:29,840
我们会坐船去欧洲并且不会再回来
We're going to Europe by ship and we're not coming back.

762
00:52:30,000 --> 00:52:33,120
齐基特的办公室 齐基特和温斯顿认识对方
Chee Kit's office. Chee Kit and Winston knew each other.

763
00:52:33,280 --> 00:52:36,800
我相信我哥哥跟一些危险人物有联系
I believe my brother was involved with some dangerous people.

764
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:38,280
一切还好吗 林先生?
Everything alright, Mr Lim?

765
00:52:38,440 --> 00:52:40,960
这是我找出杀害我丈夫的凶手的机会
This is my chance to find out who killed my husband.

